[1] Colombia ex Venezuela
Date: Sat 5 May 2018
Source: Caracol Radio [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
http://caracol.com.co/emisora/2018/05/05/sincelejo/1525538886_747460.html


The National Institute of Health (INS) has confirmed 7 cases of measles in the municipality of San Onofre, Sucre. This was announced by the secretary of Health of that department, Ramon Quintero, who informed that 4 cases are imported from Venezuela and 3 from are Venezuelan citizens residents in Colombia.

According to the official, these people were infected by their relatives. All were confirmed and presented within the same family.

Quintero also informed that until the end of April [2018], 42 other suspected cases had been ruled out in Sucre

Since the confirmation of the 1st 3 cases in San Onofre the Secretary of Sucre has intensified a campaign to detect possible cases especially among the population from Venezuela and their families. A team composed of nurses, doctors and epidemiologists conducts seminars to identify suspicious cases and undertake a house-to-house search.

The contingency plan implemented also includes vaccination for Colombians and Venezuelans in the area where the affected people live, as well as rapid coverage monitoring.

