[4] PAHO: Epidemiological Update
Date: Tue 8 May 2018
Source: PAHO, Pan American Health Organization [edited]
https://www.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_docman&task=doc_view&Itemid=270&gid=44797&lang=en


Situation Summary
-----------------
In 2018, between epidemiological week (EW) 1 and EW 18, there were 11 countries that reported 1115 confirmed cases in the Region of the Americas: Antigua and Barbuda (1 case), Argentina (3 cases), Brazil (104 cases), Canada (9 cases), Colombia (21 cases), Ecuador (3 cases), Guatemala (1 case), Mexico (4 cases), Peru (2 cases), the United States (63 cases), and Venezuela (904 cases). This number exceeds what was reported in 2017, when 4 countries in the Region reported 895 confirmed cases: Argentina (3 cases), Canada (45 cases), the United States of America (120 cases), and Venezuela (727 cases).

Following is a summary of the situation by the countries reporting measles cases in 2018.

The confirmed measles cases in Antigua and Barbuda and in Guatemala were both imported, the United Kingdom and Germany, respectively. The Antigua and Barbuda case is a 19-year-old female with rash illness on [19 Jan 2018]. The case in Guatemala is a 17-year-old female, with a 2-dose history of vaccination, rash onset [17 Jan 2018]. To date there have been no additional cases linked to these 2 imported cases.

The confirmed cases of measles in Canada and the United States are imported or associated with importation, and 70 percent of the cases were not vaccinated. The cases are distributed in 19 states and/or provinces. The highest proportion of cases corresponded to children and adolescents between 5 to19-years-old (35 percent), followed by adults 20 to 49-years-old (29 percent) and infants 6 to 11-months-old (20 percent). The identified genotypes are D8, D4, and B3. A total of 35 cases involved previous travel to 11 countries: Australia, France, India, Israel, Pakistan, Singapore, Spain, Romania, Uganda, Ukraine and the United Kingdom. ...

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Marianne Hopp

[See full report for details and references. - Mod.LK]

