[6] Viet Nam infectious disease warning
Date: Sun 6 May 2018
Source: Devdiscourse [edited]
https://www.devdiscourse.com/Article/6431-health-ministry-warns-the-people-of-infectious-disease-break/Eastpercent20and percent20Southpercent20Eastpercent20Asia


Localities across the country have detected a total 135 measles patients and 3 meningococcal meningitis cases.

The Health Ministry of Vietnam has warned the people of the possibility of infectious disease break in the summer. The Ministry of Health's Preventive Medicine Department said that this year [2018] the country has recorded around 15 000 dengue cases, which is down by 37.7 percent on-year.

While a total number of nearly 7000 hand, foot and mouth disease cases have been reported nationwide. Localities across the country have detected a total 135 measles patients and 3 meningococcal meningitis cases.

Hanoi alone has found 81 dengue fever cases, 234 hand, foot and mouth disease cases, 61 measles cases and 2 meningococcal meningitis cases. While in March [2018], Hanoi had 20--25 hand, foot and mouth disease patients on average per week. By late April [2018], the figure grew to 50--70 cases.

The Deputy Head of Vietnam National Hospital of Paediatrics' Infectious Disease Ward, Do Thein Hai said that there were no foot, hand, and mouth disease vaccines prepared, so it would be easy for patients to face serious complications which could lead to fatalities.

Dr. Truong Dinh Bac, Deputy Head of Preventive Medicine Department said that many respiratory and digestive diseases also have a high risk for a breakout. People need to take preventive measures against these diseases.

