[8] West Australia: traveler alert
Date: Wed 9 May 2018, 12:10AM
Source: The West Australian [edited]
https://thewest.com.au/news/health/wa-health-department-issues-measles-alert-for-passengers-on-adelaide-to-perth-flight-ng-b88830848z


Health authorities in WA [West Australia] have issued a new measles alert, for people who travelled on a Qantas domestic flight from Adelaide to Perth. The WA Health Department said passengers on Qantas flight QF585 from Adelaide to Perth last [Sat 5 May 2018] should be alert to an increased risk of measles. The flight left Adelaide around 2pm and arrived in Perth about 3:55 pm.

A young child who was on the flight has subsequently been confirmed to have measles, and would have been infectious to others on the plane. ...

There have now been 10 measles cases confirmed in Perth residents since mid-March [2018], including 4 adults, 5 infants too young for vaccination, and 1 teenager.

WA Health medical epidemiologist Gary Dowse said that 8 of the 10 cases were infected while travelling overseas. The imported cases have been infected in Bali, Thailand, India, Malaysia and Afghanistan.

"With high vaccination coverage, naturally occurring measles has been eliminated from WA for around 20 years but occasional cases and small outbreaks still occur - associated with tourists or WA residents who are infected overseas," Dr Dowse said.

[Byline: Cathy O'Leary]

