[9] Sudan (North Darfur)
Date: Tue 8 May 2018
Source: All Africa [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201805080943.html


Dozens of paramilitary combatants infected with measles have arrived in El Fashir academic hospital, a medical source in the hospital reported.

The medical source told Radio Dabanga that the hospital has received about 60 members of the Rapid Support Forces (RSF) on [Fri 5 May 2018] and [Sat 6 May 2018]. The hospital has set-up a centre in the northern wing to isolate the measles cases. "Even authorities are prohibited to approach them.

The source claimed that the infected combatants came from the military camp at Jadid Elseil, and the camp of the RSF, at the southern gate of El Fasher city.

Humanitarian aid organisations are known to carry out measles vaccinations among children: in 2017, they vaccinated more than 520 000 children in Sudan, according to the United Nations' humanitarian office OCHA.

