******
[11] England
Date: Mon 7 May 2018, 10:22 AM
Source: Liverpool Echo [edited]
https://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/news/liverpool-news/measles-cases-up-merseyside-how-14624833


Cases of measles have rocketed on Merseyside - with 3 times as many reports since the start of 2018 compared with last year [2017]. There have been 40 suspected cases of measles reported on Merseyside since the start of the year, according to Public Health England. This makes the reported number of cases 3.1 times higher than the 13 cases reported over the same period in 2017 and in 2016.

Among areas of Merseyside, Liverpool saw the highest number of reports in the first 17 weeks of the year [2018], with 15 - up from 4 in the same period in 2017. It was followed by Knowsley with 10 cases, up from 1, with 9 cases in Sefton, 5 in Wirral , and 1 in St Helens.

Across England and Wales 1022 suspected cases were reported to Public Health England - a much higher number than over the same period in recent years.

The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control has reported a high risk of measles in Europe, with cases being imported and exported between countries.

This is largely due to lower MMR vaccine uptake in many European countries. Romania, Italy, Germany, Greece and France are all currently experiencing large measles outbreaks.

[Byline: Claire Miller & Emilia Bona]

